getFormatedDate can return either string or null. In my return statement can I do some sort of check if its string then return it but if its null then return empty string? I was wondering if its possible to achieve using ?? operator

Yes, you can achieve the desired result using the nullish coalescing operator (`??`). Here's an updated version of your `stringifyDate` function:

```jsx
const stringifyDate = (formatedDate): string => {
  const formattedDate = getFormatedDate(formatedDate, {
    todayFormat: TODAY_FORMAT_MESSAGE,
    yesterdayFormat: YESTERDAY_FORMAT_MESSAGE,
    defaultFormat: DATE_FORMAT_MESSAGE,
  });
  return formattedDate ?? '';
};
```

In this code, the nullish coalescing operator (`??`) is used to check if `formattedDate` is `null` or `undefined`. If it is either of those, it will return an empty string (`''`). Otherwise, if `formattedDate` is a non-null/non-undefined value (such as a string), it will return that value as-is.

